#: inc/Engine/Admin/RocketInsights/Abilities/GetInsightsScore.php:50
msgid "Get Rocket Insights Score"
msgstr ""

#: inc/Engine/Admin/RocketInsights/Abilities/GetInsightsScore.php:51
msgctxt "Ability description"
msgid ""
"Returns a site-wide Rocket Insights summary with global_score, pages_monitored, is_running, and per-page results. Use include_metrics: true unless the user explicitly asks only for the global score.\n"
"Do not open or read GTmetrix report_url links. You may show them as complementary report links.\n"
"Use this when the user asks for a global score, site-wide overview, or all monitored pages. Do not use it for a specific page; use get-page-insights-score instead.\n"
"If is_running is true or any result is not completed, tell the user tests are still in progress and only show completed results. Recheck every minute until remaining results are available. Do not show status when all results are completed. Do not show is_running unless at least one page result has is_running: true.\n"
"Always open with a one-line global verdict, such as `Global score: 84/100 - 3 pages healthy, 2 need attention.` Present results using the richest available format: charts first, then a Markdown table, then structured prose.\n"
"When showing scores or metrics, use only the approved performance colors and thresholds."
msgstr ""

#: inc/Engine/Admin/RocketInsights/Abilities/GetPageInsightsScore.php:50
msgid "Get Rocket Insights Score for a Page"
msgstr ""

#: inc/Engine/Admin/RocketInsights/Abilities/GetPageInsightsScore.php:51
msgctxt "Ability description"
msgid ""
"Returns the latest Rocket Insights score for one specific URL. Requires a URI and returns score, status, report_url, and metric_data such as LCP, FCP, and TBT.\n"
"Use this when the user asks about the performance or score of one page. Do not use it for fresh tests; use retest-page-insights instead. Do not use it for all pages; use get-insights-scores instead.\n"
"If exists is false, tell the user the URL is not monitored and offer to add it with add-page-insights. This ability is read-only and does not trigger a new test.\n"
"Always open with a one-line verdict, such as `Score: 94/100 - page is healthy.` Present results using the richest available format: charts first, then a Markdown table, then structured prose.\n"
"Do not open or read GTmetrix report_url links. You may show them as complementary report links. When showing scores or metrics, use only the approved performance colors and thresholds."
msgstr ""

#: inc/Engine/Admin/RocketInsights/Abilities/GetRecommendations.php:82
msgid "Get Rocket Insights Recommendations"
msgstr ""

#: inc/Engine/Admin/RocketInsights/Abilities/GetRecommendations.php:83
msgid ""
"Returns WP Rocket's own site-specific performance recommendations.\n"
"Use this when the user asks what to improve or wants prioritized optimization suggestions. Do not use it for scores or test results; use get-insights-scores or get-page-insights-score instead.\n"
"Check the status first. If status is loading, retry in a few minutes. If status is completed, show the recommendations. If status is failed or expired, tell the user no recommendation data is available.\n"
"For each recommendation, mcp_actionable: true means it can be applied with set-option and may be suggested for activation. mcp_actionable: false means the recommendation requires a manual step."
msgstr ""

#: inc/Engine/Admin/RocketInsights/Abilities/RemovePageInsights.php:52
msgid "Remove Page Insights"
msgstr ""

#: inc/Engine/Admin/RocketInsights/Abilities/RemovePageInsights.php:53
msgctxt "Ability description"
msgid ""
"Permanently removes a URL from Rocket Insights monitoring and deletes its historical score data.\n"
"Use this only when the user explicitly asks to stop monitoring a page and accepts data deletion. Do not use it for pausing or retesting.\n"
"This action is destructive and non-idempotent. Before calling, explicitly confirm the exact URL with the user. Never remove multiple pages in bulk; require separate confirmation for each URL."
msgstr ""

#: inc/Engine/Admin/RocketInsights/Abilities/RemovePageInsights.php:67
msgid "Full URL of the page to remove from Rocket Insights monitoring."
msgstr ""

#: inc/Engine/Admin/RocketInsights/Abilities/RemovePageInsights.php:77
msgid "Indicates whether the page was successfully removed"
msgstr ""

#: inc/Engine/Admin/RocketInsights/Abilities/RemovePageInsights.php:81
msgid "Error message if the page could not be removed"
msgstr ""

#: inc/Engine/Admin/RocketInsights/Abilities/RetestPageInsights.php:75
msgid "Retest Page Insights"
msgstr ""

#: inc/Engine/Admin/RocketInsights/Abilities/RetestPageInsights.php:76
msgid ""
"Triggers a fresh Rocket Insights performance test for an already monitored URL. Requires a valid URI.\n"
"Use this when the user wants a fresh test for a monitored page. Do not call it while a test is already running.\n"
"Handle response statuses as follows: triggered means the test was queued and results should be polled with get-page-insights-score; running means a test is already in progress and should not be triggered again; not_found means the page is not tracked and add-page-insights should be offered; failed means an error occurred.\n"
"If the user wants results, wait and check every minute with get-page-insights-score, since the test may take a few minutes."
msgstr ""

#: inc/Engine/Admin/RocketInsights/Abilities/RetestPageInsights.php:99
msgid "Whether the retest was triggered"
msgstr ""

#: inc/Engine/Admin/RocketInsights/Abilities/RetestPageInsights.php:104
msgid ""
"Current job status: running = test already in flight; triggered = retest "
"queued; not_found = URL not tracked; failed = error"
msgstr ""

